It's honestly difficult to know where to start. I'll be as brief as possible. Approx 3 years ago Vivint installed solar panels on my home. However, the roof leaked again the following winter in the same spot (one of the areas they had drilled thru my ceiling). Upon inspection by a roofing company of your choice my roof was deemed "damaged beyond repair" and needed to be replaced. Roofer stated the panels never should have been installed on a roof of it's age in the first place. Vivint did, after MANY months of back and forth replace the portion of roof with panels. We had to pay for the other portion of the roof without panels at the tune of $16,000 out of our own pocket. The process for re-roofing and reinstallation of the original system was a complete nightmare when it came to coordinating with Vivint. Vivint's left hand not knowing what the right hand was doing. Throughout all of these processes I had to take time off of work, using my vacation days to facilitate to be sure things were coordinated properly. Prior to the leaking roof issue, we bought an electric car. After all, we had solar on our home! This of course had us using more power and needing more panels. June of 2017 we (foolishly) had Vivint install additional panels to meet our needs. THE PANELS STILL ARE NOT FUNCTIONAL.  I'll let you spend the time researching the variety of "reasons" why this newest system still isn't functioning. What I didn't know until about a week or two later is that the third party that, supposedly, installed the guards did a very poor job and did not install the guards on the bottom of the panels.
